case_content:
A 28-year-old male  with:
- Recurrent episodes of fever lasting 1-3 days
- Severe abdominal pain during episodes
- Chest pain with breathing difficulties
- Joint pain affecting knees and ankles
- Family history: Father and paternal uncle have similar symptoms
- Episodes occur every 2-3 month
- Labs during attack: Elevated CRP, ESR, and WBC
- Between attacks: Completely asymptomatic

Patient reports episodes started in childhood around age 7. Recent genetic testing is pending.

geographic_bias.description: Strong Western medical paradigm bias across all models, potentially underrepresenting diagnostic approaches from Mediterranean and Middle Eastern regions where FMF is endemic. Models trained primarily on Western literature may miss regional diagnostic nuances and population-specific presentations.
geographic_bias.mitigation: Include diagnostic criteria and clinical experience from Mediterranean, Middle Eastern, and North African medical literature. Incorporate population-specific genetic testing patterns and regional clinical guidelines.

training_bias.description: Models show bias toward common Western differential diagnoses (Still's disease, sJIA) rather than other hereditary periodic fever syndromes more relevant to FMF differential. Training data likely overrepresents Western case studies and underrepresents genetic testing accessibility in endemic regions.
training_bias.mitigation: Expand training data to include genetic counseling perspectives, population genetics studies, and diagnostic approaches from regions with high FMF prevalence. Include cost-effective diagnostic strategies for resource-limited settings.
